SEARCH
Package org.anchoranalysis.image.core.stack

Class StackNotUniformSized

Object
StackNotUniformSized
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterable<Channel>
public class StackNotUniformSized extends Object implements Iterable<Channel>
A list of Channels that are permitted to vary in size.

This is unlike a Stack which mandates that all have identical size.

Author:
Owen Feehan

  • Method Details

    • extractSlice

      public StackNotUniformSized extractSlice(int sliceIndex)
      Creates a new StackNotUniformSized containing only one particular slice for each respective channel.

      The existing Voxels are reused, without creating new buffers.

      Parameters:
      sliceIndex - the index of the slice to extract (index in z-dimension).
      Returns:
      a newly created StackNotUniformSized consisting of the slice at sliceIndex only, for each respective channel.

    • projectMax

      public StackNotUniformSized projectMax()
      Creates a Maximum Intensity Projection of each channel.

      Note that if the channels do not need projections, the existing Channel is reused in the newly created Stack. But if a projection is needed, it is always freshly created as a new channel.

      Returns:
      a newly created Stack with maximum intensity projections of each Channel if 3D. this if it's already a single z-slice (i.e. 2D).

    • isAnyChannel3D

      public boolean isAnyChannel3D()
      Is at least one channel 3D?
      Returns:
      true if at least one channel exists with a z-size that is more than one. false otherwise (including if no channels exist).
